    "This can be achieved only if λ * H * is close to 1 and the peak frequency lies within the PTA frequency range, implying T * ∼ 60 MeV.",
    "However, at frequencies around the peak, the signal corresponds to a power spectral density for the residuals steeper than γ ∼ 4, which cannot fit the data well.",
    "For this reason, values of Ω * 0.1 are disfavoured.",
    "For larger values of Ω *, the f 3 part of the spectrum at frequencies below δt -1 fin ∝ √ Ω * /(λ * H *) × H * (T *) can enter the PTA band with a sufficiently high amplitude.",
    "Furthermore, the distance between the break at δt -1 fin and the spectral peak at 1/λ * becomes minimal in the limit Ω * ∼ 1."
